This paper deals with sentiment analysis and emotion detection in conversation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a recurrent neural network architecture, which falls under the category of machine learning (ML), making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with multimodal functionality, which involves processing different types of data, such as text, audio, and video, making cs.CV (Computer Vision) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with fusion mechanisms, which involves combining different types of data, making cs.SD (Sound) a possible sub-category as well.
